      "author": "helderalvesappfire (Helder dos Santos Alves)",
      "cookedHtml": "<p>How can I customize the settings panel of the board view, like they did for <a href=\"https://monday.com/marketplace/82\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">Priority Cards</a>?<br />\n</p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/original/3X/7/1/7114cfa510120f19ef19a2d5d6938c2b73887d64.png\" title=\"2023-07-18_18-14\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"><img src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/optimized/3X/7/1/7114cfa510120f19ef19a2d5d6938c2b73887d64_2_459x500.png\" alt=\"2023-07-18_18-14\" width=\"459\" height=\"500\" /><div class=\"meta\"><span class=\"filename\">2023-07-18_18-14</span><span class=\"informations\">604×657 36.9 KB</span></div></a></div><p></p>"
    },
    {
      "id": 135501,
      "postNumber": 2,
      "createdAt": "2023-07-18T19:36:27.713Z",
      "author": "rachelatmonday (Rachel)",
      "cookedHtml": "<p>Hi <a class=\"mention\" href=\"/u/helderalvesappfire\">@helderalvesappfire</a>,</p>\n<p>Welcome to the community!</p>\n<p>You can configure those settings by navigating to your app feature and opening the <strong>View setup</strong> tab. From there, you can add fields that appear in the <em>View settings</em> section. Here’s some relevant <a href=\"https://developer.monday.com/apps/docs/configuring-your-app-1#configuration-modal\">documentation</a> as well!</p>\n<p></p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/original/3X/e/c/ecab12d78d291696603c1d380d4273f032e8e841.png\" title=\"View settings\"><img src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/optimized/3X/e/c/ecab12d78d291696603c1d380d4273f032e8e841_2_690x395.png\" alt=\"View settings\" width=\"690\" height=\"395\" /><div class=\"meta\"><span class=\"filename\">View settings</span><span class=\"informations\">3018×1730 349 KB</span></div></a></div><p></p>"
    }
  ]
